      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right, a very low-calorie meal can reduce the insulin needed for the night. In that case, your body may indeed be able to handle less insulin. However, it's still important to note that skipping a basal insulin dose can have unpredictable effects and may not be the best solution. Consider speaking with your healthcare provider about adjusting your basal insulin dose or using a different type of insulin for the night, such as an insulin spray.",
